explanation: This solution iterates through the bits of the input number from right to left, keeping track of the previous bit. If it finds two adjacent bits that are the same, it returns false. If it iterates through all the bits without finding any duplicates, it returns true. The time complexity is logarithmic because the number of bits in the input number is proportional to the logarithm of the number.

